#originalTopic=Debate:_Single-payer_universal_health_care
Government may set one standard of health care, but it may be inferior. Froma Harrop. "Canada's the wrong model for universal health care". Seattle Times. February 28th, 2007 - "Private competition also helps assure quality. Without an alternative, the monopolistic system becomes an "uncontested standard" that may be inferior."
